.TH YASH-EVENTSCTL 1 "July 2026" "yash-app-events 0.0.1"
.SH NAME
yash-eventsctl \- inspect and control yash-app-eventsd
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B yash-eventsctl
[--json] [--socket PATH] [--timeout-ms MS] COMMAND
.SH COMMANDS
version, status, state, shutdown, profile, events follow, capture, replay MANIFEST,
catalog status/refresh/list/install, suite evaluate PACKAGE, collection policy/status/review/compare, output
list/set/enable/remove/test, diagnostic plan, and diagnostic export.
.PP
Diagnostic export requires an exact total returned by diagnostic plan plus the
--privacy-reviewed flag. Selected --element-id crops require a frozen preview.
.PP
Output routes are machine-local and profile-scoped. Direct-command routes require an
absolute executable, do not invoke a shell, and receive compact JSON on standard input.
.PP
Catalog refresh and install use the daemon-owned fixed GitHub Profile Catalog origin.
Install requires the reviewed catalog revision and SHA-256 and leaves the profile inactive.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 success; 3 connection; 4 protocol/RPC; 5 validation; 6 timeout; 7 replay or suite regression.
.SH SEE ALSO
yash-app-eventsd(1)
